        rationale: "The USPSTF expanded HCV screening to all adults 18-79 in 2020 because direct-acting antivirals now cure HCV in >95% of patients in 8-12 weeks. Screening identifies the estimated 40% of HCV-positive individuals who are unaware of their infection, enabling curative treatment before progression to cirrhosis or hepatocellular carcinoma."
