    pearls: ["A healthy stoma should look like the inside of your cheek — beefy red, moist, and glistening; any color change toward dusky, purple, or black indicates ischemia and must be reported immediately","The stoma has no sensory nerve endings, so touching or cleaning it does not cause pain; however, peristomal skin IS innervated and will be painful if damaged","The key difference between ileostomy and colostomy care: ileostomy effluent contains active digestive enzymes that rapidly erode peristomal skin, making skin protection the highest priority","Empty the pouch when one-third to one-half full — a heavy pouch pulls on the seal, causing leakage and skin breakdown","Ileostomy patients are at HIGH risk for dehydration because the colon (where most water absorption occurs) has been bypassed","The crusting technique (powder-seal-powder-seal) is essential for managing denuded peristomal skin","Post-operative stoma size changes significantly during the first 6-8 weeks — patients must remeasure and resize their pouching system regularly"],
