        options: ["Yes — any stool specimen is acceptable","No — C. difficile testing should only be performed on UNFORMED (liquid/loose) stools; testing formed stools produces false positives from asymptomatic carriage","Only if the patient has symptoms","It depends on the test method"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "C. difficile PCR should only be performed on unformed stools (Bristol stool scale 5-7). Many people carry C. difficile asymptomatically. Testing formed stools detects carriage rather than active infection, leading to unnecessary treatment."
