        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Fecal calprotectin is a neutrophil-derived protein that is elevated in intestinal inflammation (IBD) but not in functional disorders (IBS). A level <50 mcg/g has >95% negative predictive value for IBD, effectively ruling it out and supporting an IBS diagnosis."
